{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Docs: private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model\n\n## Why\n\nThe snapshot model adds an operational requirement the old \"read the local checkout\" model\ndid not have — the server must be able to `fetch` from origin, which for private repos means\ncredentials. Operators and agents need clear guidance and clear failures.\n\n## What\n\n- Update the MCP-server setup docs to state the PRIVATE-REPO FETCH CREDENTIAL requirement:\n  the server's clone needs a credential helper / deploy key / token to fetch arbitrary refs.\n  Target docs (named so each AC is a deterministic, grep-able check): the MCP-server setup\n  section of `README.md` and `docs/jira-sync-setup.md` (and any dedicated MCP setup doc).\n- Document the descriptive credential-failure behavior (message + remedy) and that attested\n  mode fails closed while local mode still runs.\n- Document the `ref` + `source` semantics: attested (default, pinned SHA, SIGNS, records\n  `verified_at_sha`) vs local (in-place checkout, NEVER signs); the `origin/main` default.\n- Document the HMAC trust model + limits (integrity + intra-domain authenticity only; no\n  non-repudiation / public verifiability / transparency) and the in-toto Statement shape.\n- Document `REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR`, the disk-cap behavior, and the EFS/NFS flock caveat (cross-ref\n  alto-fruit-punch).\n\n## Scope\n\n- In: setup-doc credential section, error-behavior docs, ref/source + signing semantics, HMAC\n  trust-model doc, the new env/knobs — each pinned to a named doc file.\n- Out: code (S1-S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `README.md` (MCP-setup section) and `docs/jira-sync-setup.md` state the private-repo\n      fetch-credential requirement and how to supply it (grep-able for the credential section).\n- [ ] The descriptive missing-credential error (message + remedy) and the fail-closed (attested)\n      vs local-still-runs behavior are documented in a named file.\n- [ ] `ref`/`source` semantics, the `origin/main` default, AND the signs-vs-never-signs +\n      `verified_at_sha` recording are documented for CLI and MCP (named file).\n- [ ] The HMAC trust model + limits and the in-toto Statement shape are documented (named file).\n- [ ] `REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR`, disk-cap behavior, and the EFS/NFS flock caveat are documented\n      (xref alto-fruit-punch), each in a named file."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782526481746707001,"uuid":"24953c52-58a0-49c3-9996-3e6bb1e33815"}